Create a production-ready FastAPI RAG/AI module for an MVP called GreenGrid Exchange.

Project context:
GreenGrid Exchange is an electricity credit tracking and marketplace system. Each electricity credit represents 1 kWh of verified electricity. Users can register/login using User ID and MetaMask wallet ID, create electricity credits from meter readings, buy credits from marketplace, retire credits, and view audit history. Credits have source metadata such as Solar, Wind, Hydro, Coal, Gas, Thermal. Solar/Wind/Hydro are Renewable. Coal/Gas/Thermal are Fossil or traceability credits and must not be called green credits. Retired credits cannot be bought, sold, transferred, or reused.

The RAG/AI module should power an AI assistant that answers questions about:
- credit validity
- credit source classification
- whether a credit is renewable or fossil
- whether a credit is retired or available
- marketplace statistics
- audit history of a credit by ID
- user-owned credits
- document summaries
- electricity credit rules
- retirement rules
- general questions about the MVP

Tech stack:
- FastAPI
- Pydantic
- Amazon Bedrock placeholder service
- OpenSearch/Elasticsearch placeholder retrieval service
- S3 document storage placeholder
- In-memory repository for MVP data
- Modular service-based architecture

